name: howsmyair
description:
# Introduction

The purpose of our AP is to provide data regarding to the health effects of airborne pollutants.

# Overview
Our data model has three main models: Locations, Respiratory Illnesses, and Hazardous Air Pollutants (Chemicals). Instances of each model are related to instances of the other two models, providing an integrated view of the health effects of chemical air pollutants in various locations.

# Documentation

For each of the three main models in this documentation, we provide examples with and without query parameters on the left side of the page.

# Error Codes

1. HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request:
	Most errors return 400 Bad Request. A bad request, for example, will receive a response like this: 
	{"message": "Unable to decode data"} or {"message": "Unable to construct query"}

2. HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found
	The requested URL was not found on our server - check and confirm the correct URL was used.

3. HTTP/1.1 500 Internal Server Error
	General catch-all error when the server is unable to perform a request.

# Rate limit

There are no rate limits applied to calls from our API. However, don't abuse or DDOS us ;)
